{"cursor":"28780","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\ns manufactured in the early 20th century by the C.L. Hamilton Co. of\nWashington, D.C.]]\n\n'Shampoo' () is a hair care product used for the removal of oils, dirt, skin\nparticles, dandruff, environmental pollutants and other contaminant particles\nthat gradually build up in hair. The goal is to remove the unwanted build-up\nwithout stripping out so much sebum as to make hair unmanageable.\n\nEven though most modern shampoos include a conditioning component, shampooing is\nused to smooth and detangle hair that has been washed with conditioner first.\n","linknr":846,"url":"Shampoo","recorded":1362512388,"links":80,"instances":["animal","fruit","massage"],"pdf":["http://ec.europa.eu/health/ph_risk/committees/sccp/documents/out270_en.pdf","http://www.tnsmpb.tn.gov.in/images/HIBISCUS%20ROSA%20SINENSIS.pdf"],"categories":["Hindi words and phrases","Hairdressing","Personal hygiene products","Shampoos|","Toiletry","Drug delivery devices","Dosage forms","Indian inventions"],"headings":["History","Composition","Ingredient and functional claims","Health risks","Specialized shampoos","No Poo Movement","Traditional and prehistoric use","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Shampoo.jpg/275px-Shampoo.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/07/Shampoo_packet%2C_single-serving_%28cropped%29.jpg/150px-Shampoo_packet%2C_single-serving_%28cropped%29.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/48/Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg/16px-Folder_Hexagonal_Icon.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wi